                      "menu_id": 2,
                      "name": "Xiao",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3519,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/01/30/88913591/c11e8841d51eca4a0f5877567d0b1b28_8482699589027492011.png",
                      "name": "Bonanus",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3518,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/01/30/88913591/2a70abcd41f1c25b94da6c18901fc863_1288913184031380055.png",
                      "name": "Menogias",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3520,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/01/30/88913591/7280f8fc2afecab369f640ed8370390d_1087081343467272793.png",
                      "name": "Indarias",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2314,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/book/Yakshas: The Guardian Adepti_icon.png",
                      "name": "Yakshas: The Guardian Adepti",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Bosacius",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/23/237301566/bd3411f8ef5ac049d8e7a0fd615ca8f6_1591243487726148703.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Bosacius was the first Yaksha summoned by Rex Lapis, from whom he received the title Marshal Vritras. Living in Tianqiu, he was the elder brother to The Yakshas and had a strong spirit. He took the form of a man with four arms, used the power of Electro, and knew how not only to fight himself but also to lead others into battle. For this, he was highly respected. Bosacius's favorite technique was to lure the enemy and attack him at an unexpected moment. Because of the karmic debt, Bosacius lost his mind and disappeared, leaving all his wealth sealed by the Adeptal arts.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/23/237301566/9a723eb62826da5b39b435eec28c8297_1560700041360852429.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "500 years ago, the Cataclysm occurred. The monsters of the Abyss infested the seven kingdoms of Teyvat, and Liyue was no exception. To give the injured civilians a safe escape and to maintain their honor in the eyes of Rex Lapis, the Milleliths bravely fought the monsters in the Chasm, when suddenly, the four-armed Yaksha appeared on the battlefield. Having gone mad, at the decisive moment, he distracted the monsters towards himself. Together with him, the Milleliths moved deeper into the Chasm. In the course of fighting side-by-side with the Yaksha, these mortal soldiers could not escape being contaminated by karma or harmed during the slaughtering. To avoid being consumed by the darkness of constant killing, the Millelith soldiers used the timepiece to silently mark the passage of time during each battle. They fixed a unified marching pace and schedule so that one squadron of mortal soldiers would take the battlefield as the one before they retreated. This cycle of advance and retreat continued all the way to the depths of the Chasm, where yaksha and valiant soldiers both fell.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/23/237301566/90ec28a7bc8d4e51d7db9d334bd6a40d_7349214559654687848.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Bosacius, together with Boyang, Yelan's grandfather, descended into the sub-space of the Chasm, where time and space were distorted. Because of the karmic debt, Bosacius forgot his brothers and sisters, why he came to the Chasm, and even his name. In his delirium, Bosacius called Boyang either Menogias or Alatus, but the latter only patiently corrected him.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/23/237301566/2af43f3c6bf7a6db5cd8c137c3585938_2932162601249015320.jpg"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "At the cost of their lives, Boyang and Bosacius were able to seal the sub-space using the Fantastic Compass, an artifact capable of altering space and sealing monsters. Before dying, the four-armed Yaksha's mind cleared and he remembered his brothers and sisters. Bosacius remained trapped in the Chasm, and Alatus later encountered his phantom manifestation in the sub-space when he arrived in the mines to search for his missing brother.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
